"tlg0656_tlg001.T213927" [label="THES", locus="5.88.1_div", speaker="Dioscorides-Pedanius", text="ψιμύθιον δὲ γίνεται οὕτως · εἰς πιθάκνην πλατύστομον ἢ κεραμεᾶν γάστραν ἐγχέας δριμύτατον ὄξος ἀπέρεισαι μολυβδίνην πλίνθον ἐπὶ τὸ στόμα τοῦ κεραμίου, προυποκειμένου καλαμίνου ῥίπου, ἄνωθέν τε αὐτῆς ἐπίρριψον σκεπάσματα πρὸς τὸ μὴ διαπνεῖσθαι τὸ ὀξος · ὡς δʼ ἂν καταρρυεῖσα διαπέσῃ, τὸ μὲν ἐπαιωρούμενον καὶ καθαρὸν ὑγρὸν ἀπηθητέον, τὸ δὲ γλοιῶδες εἰς ἀγγεῖον ἐγχυτέον καὶ ξηραντέον ἐν ἡλίῳ. εἶτα ἀλεστέον ἐν χειρομυλίῳ ἢ λεαντέον ἄλλως καὶ σηστέον, 2 καὶ μετὰ ταῦτα τὸ λοιπὸν τοῦ στερεμνίου λεπτοποιητέον καὶ σηστέον, ἐναλλάξ τε τὰ αὐτὰ καὶ τρίτον καὶ τέταρτον ποιητέον", paraphrasis="In order for (white and effective) lead white to come about in the best variety - to be used for ophthalmological properties - as well as in worse varieties, .(In summer, ) pour most pungent vinegar into a broad-mouthed jar OR pot-bellied clay jar, .Place a leaden brick on a lattice of reeds, .Lay the lattice of reeds with the leaden brick onto the mouth of the pot, .Above, throw over covers to prevent vinegar from evaporating, .Wait until (the leaden brick), crumbling down, has strained through (the lattice), .Decant away the clean fluid that floats on top (of the vinegar after the leaden brick has crumbled down in it), .Pour the (remaining) viscous fluid into a vessel, .Let the viscous fluid dry under the sun, .Smooth the dried substance with a hand-mill OR in any way, .Sift the ground substance, .The substance that is sifted away is the better variety of (white and effective) lead white, that should be picked also for ophthalmological properties, .Thin (with a hand-mill OR in any way) and sift what remains (above the sieve) of the solid substance {, repeat, and do it again a third and fourth time}, .The substances that are sifted away at each repeated thinning and sifting are progressively worse varieties of (white and effective) lead white ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0656_tlg001", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927001" [label="ph.", phase_number="1", paraphrasis="(In summer, ) pour most pungent vinegar into a broad-mouthed jar ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927002" [label="ph.", phase_number="2", paraphrasis="Place a leaden brick on a lattice of reeds ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927003" [label="ph.", phase_number="3", paraphrasis="Lay the lattice of reeds with the leaden brick onto the mouth of the pot (i.e., of the broad-mouthed jar) ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927004" [label="ph.", phase_number="4", paraphrasis="Above, throw over covers (to prevent vinegar from evaporating) ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927005" [label="ph.", phase_number="5", paraphrasis="Wait until (the leaden brick), crumbling down, has strained through (the lattice) ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927006" [label="ph.", phase_number="6", paraphrasis="Decant away the clean fluid that floats on top (of the vinegar after the leaden brick has crumbled down in it) ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927007" [label="ph.", phase_number="7", paraphrasis="Pour the (remaining) viscous fluid into a vessel ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927008" [label="ph.", phase_number="8", paraphrasis="Let the viscous fluid dry under the sun ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927009" [label="ph.", phase_number="9", paraphrasis="Grind the dried substance with a hand-mill ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927010" [label="ph.", phase_number="10", paraphrasis="Sift the ground substance ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927011" [label="ph.", phase_number="11", paraphrasis="The substance that is sifted away is the better variety of (white and effective) lead white, that should be picked also for ophthalmological properties ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927012" [label="ph.", phase_number="12", paraphrasis="Thin (with a hand-mill) and sift what remains (above the sieve) of the solid substance {, repeat, and do it again a third and fourth time} ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.q213927013" [label="ph.", phase_number="13", paraphrasis="The substances that are sifted away at each repeated thinning and sifting are progressively worse varieties of (white and effective) lead white ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0007_tlg112.T141553" [label="THES", locus="691b", speaker="Plutarchus", text="ὅ τε μόλιβδος ... ὅς γε τριβόμενος ὄξει τὸ ψυκτικώτατον τῶν θανασίμων φαρμάκων ἐξανίησι ψιμύθιον", paraphrasis="When rubbed with vinegar, lead sends forth the most cooling of deadly drugs, i.e., lead white ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0007_tlg112", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"tlg0007_tlg112.q142329001" [label="ph.", phase_number="1", paraphrasis="Lead is rubbed with vinegar ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"tlg0007_tlg112.q142329002" [label="ph.", phase_number="2", paraphrasis="It sends forth the most cooling of deadly drugs, i.e., lead white ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.T212135" [label="THES", locus="p. 188", speaker="Caley-Earle-R., Richards-John-F.", text="performing in miniature ··· ······· ···· ········· by Theophrastus. Lead blocks were ········· ···· ····· · five per cent ······ acid solution ·· ·· open vessel, ··· the white crusts that ···· ······ ·· the blocks by corrosion ···· ······· ··· ·· ········· ·· ····· ten days. The product was ... ········ almost immediately, ··· ····· the solution had ····· ··· · few hours it absorbed enough carbon dioxide from the air ·· ····· ··· ···- ·········· ·· · ············ ······ of carbonate. The statements of Theophrastus suggest that, in the process ·· ·········, white lead formed in just this way", paraphrasis="We performed in miniature the process described by Theophrastus to produce lead white: .We supported blocks of lead just above a 5% acetic acid solution in an open vessel, .White crusts formed on the blocks {due to corrosion}, .{Repeatedly}, {at intervals of about 10 days}, we scraped off these crusts, .We identified the obtained product as a lead acetate containing only a small proportion of lead carbonate, .We dissolved this in tap water, .{Almost immediately} we observed a turbidity {due to the formation of basic lead carbonate}, .We let the solution stand for a few hours, .A considerable amount of lead carbonate precipitated {due to the solution having absorbed enough carbon dioxide from the air}, ( .We obtained lead white in the same way as in Theophrastus's process ) ", manifestation="explicit", source="caley_richards_1956", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717001" [label="ph.", phase_number="1", paraphrasis="We supported blocks of lead just above a 5% acetic acid solution in an open vessel ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717002" [label="ph.", phase_number="2", paraphrasis="White crusts formed on the blocks {due to corrosion} ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717003" [label="ph.", phase_number="3", paraphrasis="{Repeatedly}, {at intervals of about 10 days}, we scraped off these crusts ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717004" [label="ph.", phase_number="4", paraphrasis="We identified the obtained product as a lead acetate containing only a small proportion of lead carbonate ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717005" [label="ph.", phase_number="5", paraphrasis="We dissolved this in tap water ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717006" [label="ph.", phase_number="6", paraphrasis="{Almost immediately} we observed a turbidity {due to the formation of basic lead carbonate} ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717007" [label="ph.", phase_number="7", paraphrasis="We let the solution stand for a few hours ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717008" [label="ph.", phase_number="8", paraphrasis="A considerable amount of lead carbonate precipitated {due to the solution having absorbed enough carbon dioxide from the air} ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"caley_richards_1956.q163717009" [label="ph.", phase_number="9", paraphrasis="( We obtained lead white in the same way as in Theophrastus's process ) ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.T124253" [label="THES", locus="p. 71", speaker="Katsaros-T., Liritzis-Ioannis, Laskaris-N.", text="Sample PSI- 1 is the reproduced in laboratory white pow- der following Theophrastus ancient recipe On Stones. (ref. On Stones§ 56 above) . Ccommercial metallic lead cut in the shape of a brick approx. 10 cm length by 5 cm width and 2 cm thickness, hanged over within a ceramic ... out. A white powdered layer on its surface was removed by scratch, then washed in a marble mortar and ground down with marble pestle to a fine powder, following a dry out under the sun. Subsequently it was applied on a prepared wooden surface with a gypsum or calcite support", paraphrasis="We reproduced in laboratory the white powder sample PSI-1 (which is composed of cerussite and hydrocerussite, and is therefore lead white) following Theophrastus's recipe (on the preparation of lead white): .We cut commercial metallic lead in the shape of a brick {approx. 10 cm length by 5 cm width by 2 cm thickness}, .We placed vinegar on the bottom of a ceramic vessel, .We hung the brick-shaped piece of lead over the vinegar within the ceramic vessel, .We covered the vessel with a skin {approx. 1 mm (in thickness)} quasi-transparent to air (i.e., such that it breathes), .We placed the vessel under the sun, .We waited {for 10 days}, {at temperatures of average 30 °C and a range of 27-55 degrees}, .We removed the skin cover, .We took the brick-shaped lead out, .We removed the white powdered layer (thus formed) on the surface of the lead by scratching, .In a marble mortar, we washed and ground down to a fine powder the white powdered layer using a marble pestle, .We waited for it to dry out under the sun, ( .We obtained the white powder sample PSI-1 (which is composed of cerussite and hydrocerussite, and is therefore lead white) following Theophrastus's recipe (on the preparation of lead white) ), .We applied it on a prepared wooden surface with a gypsum OR calcite support ", manifestation="explicit", source="katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226001" [label="ph.", phase_number="1", paraphrasis="We cut commercial metallic lead in the shape of a brick {approx. 10 cm length by 5 cm width by 2 cm thickness} ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226002" [label="ph.", phase_number="2", paraphrasis="We placed vinegar on the bottom of a ceramic vessel ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226003" [label="ph.", phase_number="3", paraphrasis="We hung the brick-shaped piece of lead over the vinegar within the ceramic vessel ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226004" [label="ph.", phase_number="4", paraphrasis="We covered the vessel with a skin {approx. 1 mm (in thickness)} quasi-transparent to air (i.e., such that it breathes) ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226005" [label="ph.", phase_number="5", paraphrasis="We placed the vessel under the sun ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226006" [label="ph.", phase_number="6", paraphrasis="We waited {for 10 days}, {at temperatures of average 30 °C and a range of 27-55 degrees} ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226007" [label="ph.", phase_number="7", paraphrasis="We removed the skin cover ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226008" [label="ph.", phase_number="8", paraphrasis="We took the brick-shaped lead out ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226009" [label="ph.", phase_number="9", paraphrasis="We removed the white powdered layer (thus formed) on the surface of the lead by scratching ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226010" [label="ph.", phase_number="10", paraphrasis="In a marble mortar, we washed and ground down to a fine powder the white powdered layer using a marble pestle ", shape="box", color="palegreen", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226011" [label="ph.", phase_number="11", paraphrasis="We waited for it to dry out under the sun ", shape="box", color="mediumaquamarine", label_color="darkseagreen", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226012" [label="ph.", phase_number="12", paraphrasis="( We obtained the white powder sample PSI-1 (which is composed of cerussite and hydrocerussite, and is therefore lead white) following Theophrastus's recipe (on the preparation of lead white) ) ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

"katsaros_liritzis_laskaris_2010.q131226013" [label="ph.", phase_number="13", paraphrasis="We applied it on a prepared wooden surface with a gypsum support ", shape="box", color="darkseagreen", label_color="darkgrey", style="rounded,filled"];

